					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7630642#post-4002086</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7630642/scp-4577#post-4002086</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 24 Sep 2018 16:36:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MrPines</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2241229</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">spoilers&nbsp;about&nbsp;the&nbsp;thing</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>It's alluded to in the interviews that the reason the -1's go to garbage is due to the feelings of insignificance or inferiority from their lives linger, and the town is the driving force in their reanimation. They feel they don't deserve proper burials, and thus, bury themselves in garbage. Regarding the origin of the anomaly, I chose to keep it ambiguous because I feel explaining everything about the town would take away from the mystery of the town and SCP.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7630642#post-4002038</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7630642/scp-4577#post-4002038</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 24 Sep 2018 15:55:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Join my discord</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4398303</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This doesn't make sense from an realistic/anomalous point of view&#8230; The part where the dead reanimate makes the story interesting, but why would they randomly be attracted to garbage in such a way? Also, given that the citizens have full knowledge about the anomalous activity, I feel like a confidential document describing past events or a hidden cause behind the anomaly (possibly linking to a GOI) would make the story more fun/intriguing to read. -1 for now</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
